   <li><strong>Solana (SOL):</strong> Rose to $178–180, breaking above $185 could pave the way to $225.</li>\n            <li><strong>XRP:</strong> Increased over 300% in the past year, thanks to the SEC lawsuit resolution, unlocking liquidity and boosting institutional confidence.</li>\n            <li><strong>Emerging Trends:</strong> Capital rotation from Bitcoin to altcoins with higher profit potential is underway.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n</section>\n\n<section id="breaking-news-impact-section">\n    <h2><i class="fas fa-newspaper icon-color-expert-outlook"></i> Breaking News & Impact Analysis</h2>\n    <div class="report-card col-span-full">\n        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-text-secondary">\n            <li><strong>Higher-than-expected PPI report:</strong> Caused a drop in Bitcoin and reduced expectations for Fed interest rate cuts.</li>\n            <li><strong>Mixed ETF flows:</strong> Positive inflows for Bitcoin and Ethereum ETFs on Aug 13, but significant outflows for Bitcoin ETFs on Aug 11, indicating volatility and shifts in short-term sentiment.</li>\n            <li><strong>Whale movements:</strong> An inactive Bitcoin whale moving 3,000 BTC after 10 years suggests potential larger market movements.</li>\n            <li><strong>SEC and CFTC regulatory initiatives:</strong> SEC's "Project Crypto" and CFTC's "crypto sprint" signal a new era of regulatory clarity, potentially reducing uncertainty and attracting more institutions.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n</section>\n\n<section id="expert-outlook-section">\n    <h2><i class="fas fa-lightbulb icon-color-outlook"></i> Expert Opinions & Diverse Sentiment</h2>\n    <div class="report-card col-span-full">\n        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-text-secondary">\n            <li><strong>Institutional Analysts (JPMorgan):</strong> Shifted to a bullish stance on the crypto market in 2025, predicting Bitcoin will outperform gold in the second half of the year, driven by corporate demand and support from US states.</li>\n            <li><strong>Native Crypto Experts:</strong>\n                <ul class="list-circle list-inside ml-4">\n                    <li>Michael Saylor (Strategy) continues to express unwavering confidence in Bitcoin's long-term trajectory.</li>\n                    <li>Pierre Rochard suggests that Bitcoin's traditional 4-year cycle is "dead," with institutional demand now shaping the market, overshadowing the impact of halving events.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </li>\n            <li><strong>Social Media Sentiment:</strong> The Fear & Greed Index (60) indicates that positive sentiment still prevails despite recent price corrections.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n</section>\n\n<section id="conclusion-section">\n    <h2><i class="fas fa-bullseye icon-color-outlook"></i> Conclusion and Outlook</h2>\n    <div class="report-card col-span-full">\n        <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-line text-blue-500"></i> Short-term Outlook (1-4 weeks)</h3>\n        <p>The cryptocurrency market is likely to continue consolidating after the recent price surge. Bitcoin's price may test support levels around $110,000 - $112,000. Macroeconomic factors, especially inflation data and signals from the Fed, will continue to influence market sentiment. Mixed ETF flows indicate both buying and selling pressure.</p>\n        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">\n            <li><strong>Bullish Scenario:</strong> If Bitcoin holds above $118,000 and ETF inflows remain positive, especially from large institutions, the price could aim to retest its record high of $124,517 and then $128,000.</li>\n            <li><strong>Sideways Scenario:</strong> The market could fluctuate between $110,000 - $122,000 if there is no breakthrough macroeconomic or regulatory news.</li>\n            <li><strong>Bearish Scenario:</strong> If Bitcoin fails to hold the $110,000 - $112,000 support levels, or if inflation data continues to be "hotter" than expected, the price could drop further, potentially testing $100,000.</li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h3 class="mt-6"><i class="fas fa-chart-area text-green-500"></i> Medium-term Outlook (1-3 months)</h3>\n        <p>The medium-term outlook heavily depends on Fed policy and regulatory clarity. If the Fed continues its trend of interest rate cuts (albeit slower than expected) and the legal framework becomes clearer, institutional adoption will continue to increase, supporting the market. JPMorgan predicts Bitcoin will outperform gold in the second half of 2025.</p>\n\n        <h3 class="mt-6"><i class="fas fa-chart-pie text-purple-500"></i> Long-term Vision (6-12 months)</h3>\n        <p>In the long term, technological developments (e.g., Ethereum's Layer 2), the maturation of the DeFi and NFT ecosystems, along with the establishment of robust institutional infrastructure, will be key drivers. The stability of the global regulatory framework will be crucial to attracting more capital and users. Experts' views on Bitcoin becoming a reserve asset for major corporations remain an important long-term vision.</p>\n\n        <h3 class="mt-6"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle text-red-500"></i> Risk Assessment</h3>\n        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">\n            <li><strong>Fed Policy Shifts:</strong> Any "hawkish" signals from the Fed due to persistent inflation could put significant pressure on risk assets.</li>\n            <li><strong>Regulatory Risks:</strong> Despite positive developments, unexpected enforcement actions or tighter regulations could create uncertainty.</li>\n            <li><strong>Market Volatility:</strong> Cryptocurrencies remain a highly volatile market.</li>\n            <li><strong>Correlation with Traditional Markets:</strong> An increasing correlation with traditional stock markets means cryptocurrencies could be affected by broader sell-offs.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </div>\n</section>\n\n<section id="data-validation-section">\n    <h2><i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-500"></i> Data Validation Summary</h2>\n    <div class="report-card col-span-full">\n        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-600">VALIDATION RESULT: <span class="text-2xl">PASS</span></p>\n        <p class="text-text-secondary">All critical data (BTC Price, 24h Change, Fear & Greed Index) are within acceptable thresholds compared to real-time system data. Other metrics not available from search were prioritized from real-time data. Additional analytical information has been compiled from various reputable sources.</p>\n    </div>\n</section>	\N	2025-08-15 09:26:11.027076
5	<main class="crypto-report">\n    <section id="summary-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-chart-line" style="color: var(--icon-color-summary);"></i> Tóm tắt Điều hành</h2>\n        <div class="report-card">\n            <p>Thị trường tiền điện tử đang trải qua một đợt điều chỉnh đáng kể sau chuỗi ngày tăng giá mạnh mẽ. <strong>Bitcoin (BTC) đã giảm 4,03% trong 24 giờ qua, giao dịch quanh mức <span class="highlight-value">$118.802 USD</span></strong>, kéo theo sự sụt giảm của hầu hết các altcoin lớn.</p>\n            <p>Tổng vốn hóa thị trường tiền điện tử toàn cầu giảm hơn 3%, từ <span class="highlight-value">$4,19 nghìn tỷ USD</span> xuống còn <span class="highlight-value">$4,02 nghìn tỷ USD</span>.</p>\n            <p>Nguyên nhân chính là do dữ liệu Chỉ số Giá Sản xuất (PPI) tại Mỹ tháng 7 tăng 0,9%, cao hơn dự báo, làm lung lay kỳ vọng cắt giảm lãi suất của Cục Dự trữ Liên bang (Fed) vào tháng 9. Điều này đã kích hoạt làn sóng thanh lý vị thế đòn bẩy lớn, với <strong>hơn <span class="highlight-value">$1,1 tỷ USD</span> bị thanh lý trong 24 giờ</strong> (chủ yếu là vị thế mua).</p>\n            <p>Mặc dù có sự điều chỉnh, tâm lý thị trường vẫn duy trì ở mức <strong>"Tham lam" (Chỉ số Sợ hãi & Tham lam là <span class="highlight-value">60</span>)</strong>. Triển vọng dài hạn vẫn lạc quan, với các dự báo Bitcoin có thể vượt <span class="highlight-value">$4,81 triệu USD</span> vào năm 2036 và hoạt động tích lũy BTC của các tổ chức như MicroStrategy vẫn tiếp diễn.</p>\n            <p><strong>Ngắn hạn</strong>, thị trường có khả năng tiếp tục biến động do chờ đợi dữ liệu vĩ mô và áp lực từ hợp đồng quyền chọn đáo hạn.</p>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id="market-psychology-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-chart-pie" style="color: var(--icon-color-on-chain-sentiment);"></i> Phân tích Tâm lý Thị trường</h2>\n        <div class="content-grid">\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Chỉ số Sợ hãi & Tham lam</h3>\n        