             <td data-label="24h Thay đổi" class="negative-text">-6.17%</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td data-label="Coin">BNB</td>\n                            <td data-label="Giá">$868.79</td>\n                            <td data-label="24h Thay đổi" class="positive-text">+0.5% (Đạt ATH)</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td data-label="Coin">Dogecoin (DOGE)</td>\n                            <td data-label="Giá">N/A</td>\n                            <td data-label="24h Thay đổi" class="negative-text">-10%+</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td data-label="Coin">Shiba Inu (SHIB)</td>\n                            <td data-label="Giá">N/A</td>\n                            <td data-label="24h Thay đổi" class="negative-text">-10%+</td>\n                        </tr>\n                    </tbody>\n                </table>\n            </div>\n            <p>Lĩnh vực Hạ tầng Vật lý Phi tập trung (DePIN) được dự báo sẽ có bước đột phá vào năm 2025.</p>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id="breaking-news-impact-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-newspaper" style="color: var(--icon-color-expert-outlook);"></i> Tin Tức Nổi bật & Phân tích Tác động</h2>\n        <div class="report-card full-width">\n            <div class="table-container">\n                <table class="crypto-table">\n                    <thead>\n                        <tr>\n                            <th>Tin tức</th>\n                            <th>Tác động (Thang 1-10)</th>\n                            <th>Ảnh hưởng</th>\n                        </tr>\n                    </thead>\n                    <tbody>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td data-label="Tin tức">Dữ liệu PPI Mỹ tăng nóng</td>\n                            <td data-label="Tác động">9/10</td>\n                            <td data-label="Ảnh hưởng" class="negative-text">Tiêu cực ngay lập tức (dump thị trường, thanh lý)</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td data-label="Tin tức">SEC hoãn quyết định ETF Solana</td>\n                            <td data-label="Tác động">6/10</td>\n                            <td data-label="Ảnh hưởng" class="negative-text">Tiêu cực vừa phải đến tâm lý altcoin, trì hoãn dòng tiền</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td data-label="Tin tức">Quỹ Ethereum bán ETH</td>\n                            <td data-label="Tác động">5/10</td>\n                            <td data-label="Ảnh hưởng" class="negative-text">Tiêu cực đến tâm lý ETH và altcoin trong ngắn hạn</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td data-label="Tin tức">Sắc lệnh của Tổng thống Trump về 401(k) và crypto</td>\n                            <td data-label="Tác động">8/10</td>\n                            <td data-label="Ảnh hưởng" class="positive-text">Tích cực dài hạn, mở rộng cơ sở nhà đầu tư</td>\n                        </tr>\n                    </tbody>\n                </table>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id="expert-outlook-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-brain" style="color: var(--icon-color-outlook);"></i> Ý kiến Chuyên gia & Tâm lý Đa chiều</h2>\n        <div class="content-grid">\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Quan điểm Phố Wall & Chuyên gia Crypto</h3>\n                <ul>\n                    <li><strong>Phố Wall:</strong> Vàng vẫn là kênh trú ẩn an toàn hơn Bitcoin khi thị trường chứng khoán biến động mạnh (Bloomberg Intelligence). ETH <strong><span class="highlight-value">$6.000 USD</span></strong> khả thi nếu cầu tổ chức giữ vững (Fundstrat).</li>\n                    <li><strong>Chuyên gia Crypto:</strong> Michael Saylor (Strategy) dự đoán Bitcoin có thể tăng lên <strong><span class="highlight-value">$21 triệu USD</span></strong> trong 21 năm tới. Các nhà phân tích nhận định Bitcoin chỉ mới ở giai đoạn thứ hai của chu kỳ tăng giá, có thể kéo dài đến quý 3 năm 2025.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </div>\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Nghiên cứu Học thuật & Phân tích On-chain</h3>\n                <ul>\n                    <li><strong>Nghiên cứu Học thuật:</strong> Nghiên cứu từ Satoshi Action Education dự báo <strong><span class="highlight-value">75%</span></strong> khả năng Bitcoin vượt <strong><span class="highlight-value">$4,81 triệu USD</span></strong> vào tháng 4 năm 2036.</li>\n                    <li><strong>Phân tích On-chain:</strong> Tỷ lệ MVRV của Bitcoin chưa quá nóng. Giá Bitcoin có thể giảm xuống <strong><span class="highlight-value">$110.000 USD</span></strong> trước khi có động thái hướng đến mức cao mới. Chỉ <strong><span class="highlight-value">14,5%</span></strong> tổng số BTC hiện đang nằm trên các sàn giao dịch, cho thấy "tiền thông minh" đang tích lũy.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id="conclusion-outlook-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-chart-bar" style="color: var(--icon-color-summary);"></i> Kết luận và Triển vọng</h2>\n        <div class="report-card full-width">\n            <p>Thị trường tiền điện tử đang ở một thời điểm quan trọng, chịu tác động từ cả yếu tố vĩ mô và động lực nội tại. Sự điều chỉnh gần đây do dữ liệu PPI của Mỹ đã làm tăng áp lực bán, nhưng tâm lý thị trường vẫn duy trì lạc quan trong bối cảnh kỳ vọng về chính sách tiền tệ nới lỏng của Fed và dòng tiền tổ chức tiếp tục đổ vào.</p>\n\n            <h3>Triển vọng Ngắn hạn (1-4 tuần)</h3>\n            <ul>\n                <li><strong>Kịch bản giảm giá:</strong> Thị trường có thể tiếp tục chịu áp lực bán do dữ liệu PPI tiêu cực và áp lực đáo hạn quyền chọn lớn. Bitcoin có thể kiểm tra lại các mức hỗ trợ quan trọng như <strong><span class="highlight-value">$118.000 USD</span></strong>, và nếu không giữ được, có thể giảm sâu hơn về <strong><span class="highlight-value">$116.000 USD</span></strong> hoặc <strong><span class="highlight-value">$112.000 USD</span></strong>. Altcoin có thể bị ảnh hưởng nặng hơn.</li>\n                <li><strong>Kịch bản đi ngang:</strong> Bitcoin có thể bước vào giai đoạn tích lũy ngang để ổn định đà tăng nếu giữ vững vùng hỗ trợ <strong><span class="highlight-value">$118.000 USD</span></strong>, chờ đợi các tín hiệu rõ ràng hơn từ dữ liệu kinh tế vĩ mô.</li>\n            </ul>\n\n            <h3>Triển vọng Trung hạn (1-3 tháng)</h3>\n            <ul>\n                <li>Thị trường có thể tiếp tục phân hóa, với dòng vốn luân chuyển giữa Bitcoin và các altcoin.</li>\n                <li>Kỳ vọng về việc Fed cắt giảm lãi suất vào tháng 9 vẫn là một động lực tiềm năng cho các tài sản rủi ro.</li>\n                <li>Sự chấp thuận các quỹ ETF Solana vào tháng 10 có thể tạo ra một làn sóng tăng giá mới cho hệ sinh thái Solana.</li>\n            </ul>\n\n            <h3>Triển vọng Dài hạn (6-12 tháng)</h3>\n            <ul>\n                <li>Triển vọng dài hạn vẫn rất tích cực nhờ sự chấp nhận ngày càng tăng của các tổ chức và doanh nghiệp.</li>\n                <li>Sắc lệnh của Tổng thống Trump cho phép quỹ hưu trí đầu tư vào crypto có thể mở ra một nguồn vốn khổng lồ cho thị trường.</li>\n                <li>Các dự báo dài hạn cho Bitcoin vẫn rất lạc quan, với mục tiêu giá hàng triệu USD trong tương lai.</li>\n                <li>Sự phát triển của các lĩnh vực mới như DePIN cũng sẽ thúc đẩy thị trường.</li>\n            </ul>\n\n            <h3>Đánh giá Rủi ro</h3>\n            <ul>\n                <li><strong>Rủi ro vĩ mô:</strong> Dữ liệu lạm phát cao hơn dự kiến có thể khiến Fed trì hoãn hoặc thắt chặt chính sách tiền tệ.</li>\n                <li><strong>Rủi ro thanh lý:</strong> Khối lượng thanh lý lớn cho thấy thị trường vẫn nhạy cảm với biến động giá.</li>\n                <li><strong>Rủi ro quy định:</strong> Các quy định vẫn có thể gây ra biến động thị trường (ví dụ: SEC hoãn ETF).</li>\n                <li><strong>Rủi ro thanh khoản:</strong> Nhu cầu từ các tổ chức tăng trong khi nguồn cung Bitcoin hạn chế có thể dẫn đến khủng hoảng thanh khoản, gây biến động giá lớn.</li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n</main>	#report-container {\n    /* General theme colors for the report container itself */\n    background: linear-gradient(to bottom right, var(--bg-gradient-start), var(--bg-gradient-end));\n    color: var(--text-primary);\n    padding: 2rem; /* Add some padding around the report content */\n    border-radius: 8px; /* Slightly rounded corners for the main container */\n}\n\n#report-container .report-card {\n    /* Card styling - background, border, shadow */\n    background-color: var(--card-bg);\n    border: 1px solid var(--card-border);\n    box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);\n    border-radius: 0.5rem; /* Rounded corners for cards */\n    padding: 1.5rem; /* Internal padding for card content */\n    backdrop-filter: blur(5px); /* Subtle blur for a modern feel */\n    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(5px); /* For Safari support */\n}\n\n/* 1. 🎨 CRYPTO THEME COLORS */\n#report-container .crypto-positive,\n#report-container .positive-text {\n    color: var(--positive-color); /* Success green */\n}\n\n#report-container .crypto-negative,\n#report-container .negative-text {\n    color: var(--negative-color); /* Danger red */\n}\n\n#report-container .bitcoin-accent {\n    color: var(--icon-color-btc); /* Bitcoin orange */\n}\n\n#report-container .ethereum-accent {\n    color: var(--icon-color-eth); /* Ethereum blue */\n}\n\n/* 2. 📊 DATA VISUALIZATION COLORS */\n#report-container td.positive {\n    color: var(--positive-color);\n    font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n#report-container td.negative {\n    color: var(--negative-color);\n    font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n#report-container .highlight-value {\n    color: var(--accent-color); /* Making key numbers stand out */\n    font-weight: 700; /* Bold for emphasis */\n}\n\n/* Table specific styling for better readability and crypto feel */\n#report-container .crypto-table {\n    width: 100%;\n    border-collapse: collapse;\n    margin-top: 1rem;\n    font-size: 0.95rem;\n}\n\n#report-container .crypto-table th,\n#report-container .crypto-table td {\n    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;\n    text-align: left;\n    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);\n    color: var(--text-secondary);\n}\n\n#report-container .crypto-table th {\n    background-color: var(--bg-secondary); /* A slightly different background for headers */\n    color: var(--text-primary);\n    font-weight: 600;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    letter-spacing: 0.05em;\n}\n\n#report-container .crypto-table tbody tr:hover {\n    background-color: var(--table-row-hover-bg); /* Hover effect for table rows */\n}\n\n/* 3. 🔥 SPECIAL CONTENT STYLING */\n\n/* Bull/Bear/Sideway card styling (assuming these classes are added to .report-card) */\n#report-container .report-card.bull-market {\n    background-color: var(--bull-card-bg);\n    border-color: var(--positive-color); /* A subtle border accent */\n}\n\n#report-container .report-card.bear-market {\n    background-color: var(--bear-card-bg);\n    border-color: var(--negative-color); /* A subtle border accent */\n}\n\n#report-container .report-card.sideway-market {\n    background-color: var(--sideway-card-bg);\n    border-color: var(--neutral-color); /* A subtle border accent */\n}\n\n/* Fear & Greed levels text emphasis */\n#report-container #fear-greed-text-analysis p strong .highlight-value {\n    /* This will override the general highlight-value for F&G specifically if needed */\n    /* For example, if the value is 60 (Greed), you might want to use the greed color */\n    /* This requires dynamic class application based on value, but for static CSS,\n       we'll rely on the general highlight-value or a more specific class if available. */\n    /* For now, the general highlight-value is sufficient. */\n}\n\n/* 4. 💡 CONTENT-SPECIFIC HIGHLIGHTS */\n\n/* Section headers with icons */\n#report-container section h2 {\n    color: var(--text-primary);\n    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-color);\n    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;\n    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    font-size: 1.75rem; /* Adjusted for visual hierarchy */\n    font-weight: 700;\n}\n\n#report-container section h2 i.fas {\n    margin-right: 0.75rem;\n    font-size: 1.5rem;\n}\n\n/* Card sub-headers with crypto icons */\n#report-container .report-card h3 {\n    color: var(--text-accent);\n    margin-bottom: 1rem;\n    font-size: 1.25rem; /* Adjusted for visual hierarchy */\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n#report-container .report-card h3 i.fab {\n    margin-right: 0.6rem;\n    font-size: 1.25rem;\n}\n\n/* List item styling for better readability */\n#report-container .report-card ul {\n    list-style: none;\n    padding-left: 0;\n}\n\n#report-container .report-card ul li {\n    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\n    line-height: 1.6;\n    color: var(--text-secondary);\n    position: relative;\n    padding-left: 1.5rem; /* Space for custom bullet */\n}\n\n#report-container .report-card ul li::before {\n    content: '•'; /* Custom bullet point */\n    color: var(--accent-color); /* Accent color for bullets */\n    position: absolute;\n    left: 0;\n    font-weight: bold;\n    font-size: 1.2em;\n    line-height: 1;\n}\n\n/* Special styling for breaking news table */\n#report-container #breaking-news-impact-section .crypto-table tbody tr {\n    /* Add a subtle left border to highlight news items */\n    border-left: 4px solid var(--cadet-blue-color);\n}\n\n#report-container #breaking-news-impact-section .crypto-table td[data-label="Tác động"] {\n    font-weight: 700;\n    color: var(--text-accent); /* Make impact numbers stand out */\n}\n\n/* Specific styling for the conclusion section for emphasis */\n#report-container #conclusion-outlook-section h3 {\n    color: var(--royal-blue-color); /* A distinct color for sub-sections in conclusion */\n    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border-color);\n    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;\n    margin-top: 1.5rem;\n    font-size: 1.15rem;\n}\n\n/* Risk assessment points in conclusion */\n#report-container #conclusion-outlook-section ul li::before {\n    content: '⚠'; /* Warning icon for risks */\n    color: var(--negative-color); /* Red bullet for risks */\n    font-size: 1em;\n}\n\n/* Styling for the main report container background gradient */\n#report-container {\n    background: linear-gradient(to bottom right, var(--bg-gradient-start), var(--bg-gradient-end));\n}	// report.js\n\n/**\n * Helper function to extract JSON data from the preceding HTML comment.\n * Assumes the comment is directly before the container div and follows the format:\n * <!-- CHART_DATA: {...} -->\n * @param {HTMLElement} container - The DOM element whose preceding sibling is the comment.\n * @returns {object|null} Parsed JSON data or null if not found/invalid.\n */\nfunction getChartDataFromComment(container) {\n    if (!container || !container.previousSibling) {\n        // console.warn("Container or its previous sibling not found for chart data:", container ? container.id : 'unknown');\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    const commentNode = container.previousSibling;\n\n    // Ensure it's a comment node and contains CHART_DATA\n    if (commentNode.nodeType === Node.COMMENT_NODE) {\n        const commentText = commentNode.nodeValue.trim();\n        const dataPrefix = "CHART_DATA: ";\n        if (commentText.startsWith(dataPrefix)) {\n            try {\n                const jsonString = commentText.substring(dataPrefix.length);\n                return JSON.parse(jsonString);\n            } catch (e) {\n                console.error("Error parsing CHART_DATA JSON for container:", container.id, e);\n                return null;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    // console.warn("No valid CHART_DATA comment found before container:", container.id);\n    return null;\n}\n\n/**\n * Initializes and draws the Fear & Greed Gauge chart.\n * @param {string} language - 'vi' for Vietnamese, 'en' for English.\n */\nfunction initializeFearGreedGauge_report(language) {\n    const lang = language;\n    // Determine container ID based on language (assuming -en suffix for English containers)\n    const id = lang === 'en' ? 'fear-greed-gauge-container-en' : 'fear-greed-gauge-container';\n    const container = document.getElementById(id);\n    if (!container) return; // Exit if container not found\n\n    const chartData = getChartDataFromComment(container);\n    if (!chartData) return; // Exit if chart data not found or invalid\n\n    const value = chartData.value;\n    const baseConfig = chartData.config; // Base config from HTML comment\n\n    // Language-specific labels for the gauge segments\n    const config_vi_labels = {\n        segments: [\n            {limit: 25, label: 'Cực kỳ sợ hãi'},\n            {limit: 45, label: 'Sợ hãi'},\n            {limit: 55, label: 'Trung tính'},\n            {limit: 75, label: 'Tham lam'},\n            {limit: 100, label: 'Cực kỳ tham lam'}\n        ]\n    };\n\n    const config_en_labels = {\n        segments: [\n            {limit: 25, label: 'Extreme Fear'},\n            {limit: 45, label: 'Fear'},\n            {limit: 55, label: 'Neutral'},\n            {limit: 75, label: 'Greed'},\n            {limit: 100, label: 'Extreme Greed'}\n        ]\n    };\n\n    const langLabels = lang === 'en' ? config_en_labels : config_vi_labels;\n\n    // Create final config by merging base config with language-specific labels.\n    // This preserves colors and other properties from baseConfig while updating labels.\n    const finalConfig = { ...baseConfig };\n    if (finalConfig.segments && langLabels.segments) {\n        finalConfig.segments = finalConfig.segments.map((segment, index) => ({\n            ...segment,\n            label: langLabels.segments[index].label // Override label with language-specific one\n        }));\n    }\n\n    createGauge(container, value, finalConfig);\n}\n\n/**\n * Initializes and draws the Bitcoin Dominance Doughnut chart.\n * @param {string} language - 'vi' for Vietnamese, 'en' for English.\n */\nfunction initializeBTCDominance_report(language) {\n    const lang = language;\n    const id = lang === 'en' ? 'btc-dominance-doughnut-container-en' : 'btc-dominance-doughnut-container';\n    const container = document.getElementById(id);\n    if (!container) return;\n\n    const chartData = getChartDataFromComment(container);\n    if (!chartData) return;\n\n    // Deep copy data to avoid modifying the original chartData.data directly\n    const data = chartData.data.map(item => ({ ...item }));\n    const baseConfig = chartData.config;\n\n    // Language-specific labels for data segments and chart title\n    const data_vi_labels = [\n        {label: 'Bitcoin'},\n        {label: 'Altcoins'}\n    ];\n    const data_en_labels = [\n        {label: 'Bitcoin'},\n        {label: 'Altcoins'} // "Altcoins" is commonly used in English too\n    ];\n\n    const config_vi_title = { title: 'BTC.D' }; // Abbreviation, usually not translated\n    const config_en_title = { title: 'BTC.D' };\n\n    const langDataLabels = lang === 'en' ? data_en_labels : data_vi_labels;\n    const langConfigTitle = lang === 'en' ? config_en_title : config_vi_title;\n\n    // Apply language-specific labels to the data array\n    data.forEach((item, index) => {\n        if (langDataLabels[index] && langDataLabels[index].label) {\n            item.label = langDataLabels[index].label; // Override label with language-specific one\n        }\n    });\n\n    // Create final config by merging base config with language-specific title\n    const finalConfig = { ...baseConfig, ...langConfigTitle };\n\n    createDoughnutChart(container, data, finalConfig);\n}\n\n/**\n * Initializes and draws the Liquidation Bar Chart.\n * @param {string} language - 'vi' for Vietnamese, 'en' for English.\n */\nfunction initializeLiquidationBar_report(language) {\n    const lang = language;\n    const id = lang === 'en' ? 'liquidation-bar-chart-container-en' : 'liquidation-bar-chart-container';\n    const container = document.getElementById(id);\n    if (!container) return;\n\n    const chartData = getChartDataFromComment(container);\n    if (!chartData) return;\n\n    // Deep copy data to avoid modifying the original chartData.data directly\n    const data = chartData.data.map(item => ({ ...item }));\n    const baseOptions = chartData.options;\n\n    // Language-specific labels for bar data and y-axis label\n    const data_vi_labels = [\n        {label: 'Vị thế Long'},\n        {label: 'Vị thế Short'}\n    ];\n    const data_en_labels = [\n        {label: 'Long Positions'},\n        {label: 'Short Positions'}\n    ];\n\n    const options_vi_labels = { yAxisLabel: 'USD' }; // USD is universal\n    const options_en_labels = { yAxisLabel: 'USD' };\n\n    const langDataLabels = lang === 'en' ? data_en_labels : data_vi_labels;\n    const langOptionsLabels = lang === 'en' ? options_en_labels : options_vi_labels;\n\n    // Apply language-specific labels to the data array\n    data.forEach((item, index) => {\n        if (langDataLabels[index] && langDataLabels[index].label) {\n            item.label = langDataLabels[index].label; // Override label with language-specific one\n        }\n    });\n\n    // Create final options by merging base options with language-specific yAxisLabel\n    const finalOptions = { ...baseOptions, ...langOptionsLabels };\n\n    createBarChart(container, data, finalOptions);\n}\n\n/**\n * Initializes and draws the RSI Gauge chart.\n * @param {string} language - 'vi' for Vietnamese, 'en' for English.\n */\nfunction initializeRSIGauge_report(language) {\n    const lang = language;\n    const id = lang === 'en' ? 'rsi-gauge-container-en' : 'rsi-gauge-container';\n    const container = document.getElementById(id);\n    if (!container) return;\n\n    const chartData = getChartDataFromComment(container);\n    if (!chartData) return;\n\n    const value = chartData.value;\n    const baseConfig = chartData.config;\n\n    // Language-specific labels for the gauge segments\n    const config_vi_labels = {\n        segments: [\n            {limit: 30, label: 'Quá bán'},\n            {limit: 70, label: 'Trung tính'},\n            {limit: 100, label: 'Quá mua'}\n        ]\n    };\n\n    const config_en_labels = {\n        segments: [\n            {limit: 30, label: 'Oversold'},\n            {limit: 70, label: 'Neutral'},\n            {limit: 100, label: 'Overbought'}\n        ]\n    };\n\n    const langLabels = lang === 'en' ? config_en_labels : config_vi_labels;\n\n    // Create final config by merging base config with language-specific labels\n    const finalConfig = { ...baseConfig };\n    if (finalConfig.segments && langLabels.segments) {\n        finalConfig.segments = finalConfig.segments.map((segment, index) => ({\n            ...segment,\n            label: langLabels.segments[index].label // Override label with language-specific one\n        }));\n    }\n\n    createGauge(container, value, finalConfig);\n}\n\n/**\n * Initializes and draws the Bitcoin Price Line Chart.\n * @param {string} language - 'vi' for Vietnamese, 'en' for English.\n */\nfunction initializeBTCPriceLine_report(language) {\n    const lang = language;\n    // Note: The provided HTML does not have an '-en' suffix for this container,\n    // so we use the base ID directly.\n    const id = 'btc-price-line-chart-container';\n    const container = document.getElementById(id);\n    if (!container) return;\n\n    const chartData = getChartDataFromComment(container);\n    if (!chartData) return;\n\n    const data = chartData.data;\n    const baseOptions = chartData.options;\n\n    // For line chart, valuePrefix/Suffix are typically universal symbols like '$'.\n    // No specific labels or text to translate within data or options for this chart.\n    // We still define options_vi and options_en as per the requirement, even if identical.\n    const options_vi = {\n        color: baseOptions.color,\n        valuePrefix: baseOptions.valuePrefix,\n        valueSuffix: baseOptions.valueSuffix\n    };\n    const options_en = {\n        color: baseOptions.color,\n        valuePrefix: baseOptions.valuePrefix,\n        valueSuffix: baseOptions.valueSuffix\n    };\n\n    const finalOptions = lang === 'en' ? options_en : options_vi;\n\n    createLineChart(container, data, finalOptions);\n}\n\n/**\n * Main function to initialize all visual charts for the crypto report.\n * It determines the current language and passes it to individual chart functions.\n * This function does NOT register event listeners. It should be called by an external app\n * when charts need to be initialized or redrawn (e.g., on language change).\n * @param {string} [language=undefined] - Optional language override ('vi' or 'en').\n *                                        If not provided, it attempts to read from window.languageManager.\n */\nfunction initializeAllVisuals_report(language = undefined) {\n    // Determine the language: use provided parameter, then window.languageManager, else default to 'vi'.\n    const lang = language || window.languageManager?.currentLanguage || 'vi';\n\n    // Call all chart initialization functions, passing the determined language.\n    initializeFearGreedGauge_report(lang);\n    initializeBTCDominance_report(lang);\n    initializeLiquidationBar_report(lang);\n    initializeRSIGauge_report(lang);\n    initializeBTCPriceLine_report(lang);\n    // Add calls to other chart initialization functions here as they are implemented.\n}	<main class="crypto-report">\n    <section id="summary-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-chart-line" style="color: var(--icon-color-summary);"></i> Executive Summary</h2>\n        <div class="report-card">\n            <p>The cryptocurrency market is undergoing a significant correction after a strong bullish streak. <strong>Bitcoin (BTC) has dropped 4.03% in the past 24 hours, trading around <span class="highlight-value">$118,802 USD</span></strong>, dragging down most major altcoins.</p>\n            <p>The total global cryptocurrency market capitalization decreased by over 3%, from <span class="highlight-value">$4.19 trillion USD</span> to <span class="highlight-value">$4.02 trillion USD</span>.</p>\n            <p>The main reason is the higher-than-forecasted 0.9% increase in the US Producer Price Index (PPI) data for July, shaking expectations for a Federal Reserve (Fed) interest rate cut in September. This triggered a wave of large leveraged position liquidations, with <strong>over <span class="highlight-value">$1.1 billion USD</span> liquidated in 24 hours</strong> (mostly long positions).</p>\n            <p>Despite the correction, market sentiment remains at <strong>"Greed" (Fear & Greed Index is <span class="highlight-value">60</span>)</strong>. The long-term outlook remains optimistic, with forecasts of Bitcoin potentially exceeding <span class="highlight-value">$4.81 million USD</span> by 2036 and continued BTC accumulation by institutions like MicroStrategy.</p>\n            <p><strong>In the short term</strong>, the market is likely to remain volatile due to anticipation of macroeconomic data and pressure from expiring options contracts.</p>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id="market-psychology-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-chart-pie" style="color: var(--icon-color-on-chain-sentiment);"></i> Market Sentiment Analysis</h2>\n        <div class="content-grid">\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Fear & Greed Index</h3>\n                <!-- CHART_DATA: {\n                  "type": "gauge",\n                  "value": 60,\n                  "config": {\n                    "min": 0,\n                    "max": 100,\n                    "segments": [\n                      {"limit": 25, "color": "var(--fng-extreme-fear-color)", "label": "Cực kỳ sợ hãi"},\n                      {"limit": 45, "color": "var(--fng-fear-color)", "label": "Sợ hãi"},\n                      {"limit": 55, "color": "var(--fng-neutral-color)", "label": "Trung tính"},\n                      {"limit": 75, "color": "var(--fng-greed-color)", "label": "Tham lam"},\n                      {"limit": 100, "color": "var(--fng-extreme-greed-color)", "label": "Cực kỳ tham lam"}\n                    ]\n                  }\n                } -->\n                <div id="fear-greed-gauge-container-en" class="chart-container" aria-label="Fear and Greed Index Chart"></div>\n                <div id="fear-greed-text-analysis">\n                    <p>The current Fear & Greed Index is <strong><span class="highlight-value">60</span> ("Greed")</strong>.</p>\n                    <p>Despite the sharp price drop in the past 24 hours, market sentiment remains greedy, indicating that investors are still optimistic long-term or looking for buying opportunities.</p>\n                    <p>The divergence between declining price action and "greedy" sentiment could be a warning sign, suggesting the market may need a deeper correction.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id="technical-analysis-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-chart-line" style="color: var(--icon-color-btc-analysis);"></i> In-depth Technical Analysis</h2>\n        <div class="content-grid">\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Bitcoin Dominance (BTC.D)</h3>\n                <!-- CHART_DATA: {\n                  "type": "doughnut",\n                  "data": [\n                    {"value": 58.6, "color": "var(--icon-color-btc)", "label": "Bitcoin"},\n                    {"value": 41.4, "color": "var(--steel-blue-color)", "label": "Altcoins"}\n                  ],\n                  "config": {\n                    "title": "BTC.D",\n                    "showLegend": true,\n                    "outerRadius": 80,\n                    "innerRadius": 50\n                  }\n                } -->\n                <div id="btc-dominance-doughnut-container-en" class="chart-container" aria-label="Bitcoin Dominance Doughnut Chart"></div>\n                <div id="btc-dominance-text-analysis">\n                    <p>Bitcoin Dominance (BTC.D) is currently <strong><span class="highlight-value">58.6%</span></strong>, down 4.75%.</p>\n                    <p>This indicates that capital is shifting from Bitcoin to altcoins, creating an "altcoin season" in the short term.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Trading Volume & Liquidations (24h)</h3>\n                <!-- CHART_DATA: {\n                  "type": "bar",\n                  "data": [\n                    {"value": 790, "label": "Vị thế Long", "color": "var(--negative-color)"},\n                    {"value": 235, "label": "Vị thế Short", "color": "var(--positive-color)"}\n                  ],\n                  "options": {\n                    "valueSuffix": "M",\n                    "yAxisLabel": "USD"\n                  }\n                } -->\n                <div id="liquidation-bar-chart-container-en" class="chart-container" aria-label="Liquidation Volume Bar Chart"></div>\n                <div id="volume-analysis-text">\n                    <p>Total 24h trading volume is <strong><span class="highlight-value">$254.5 billion USD</span></strong>.</p>\n                    <p>Over <strong><span class="highlight-value">$1.1 billion USD</span></strong> has been liquidated in the past 24 hours, including <strong><span class="negative-text">$790 million USD</span> in Long positions</strong> and <strong><span class="positive-text">$235 million USD</span> in Short positions</strong>.</p>\n                    <p>This indicates that the market is undergoing a "flush out" of leveraged positions.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Bitcoin Relative Strength Index (RSI)</h3>\n                <!-- CHART_DATA: {\n                  "type": "gauge",\n                  "value": 75,\n                  "config": {\n                    "min": 0,\n                    "max": 100,\n                    "segments": [\n                      {"limit": 30, "color": "var(--rsi-oversold-color)", "label": "Quá bán"},\n                      {"limit": 70, "color": "var(--rsi-neutral-color)", "label": "Trung tính"},\n                      {"limit": 100, "color": "var(--rsi-overbought-color)", "label": "Quá mua"}\n                    ]\n                  }\n                } -->\n                <div id="rsi-gauge-container-en" class="chart-container" aria-label="Bitcoin RSI Gauge Chart"></div>\n                <div id="rsi-text-analysis">\n                    <p>After Bitcoin surpassed $123,000 USD, a bearish divergence appeared between price and the Relative Strength Index (RSI), signaling weakness.</p>\n                    <p>The estimated RSI value is currently at <strong><span class="highlight-value">75</span></strong>, indicating an overbought condition before the correction.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n\n            <div class="report-card full-width">\n                <h3>Bitcoin Price Analysis (24h)</h3>\n                <!-- CHART_DATA: {\n                  "type": "line",\n                  "data": [123400, 120500, 117400, 118802],\n                  "options": {\n                    "color": "var(--accent-color)",\n                    "valuePrefix": "$",\n                    "valueSuffix": ""\n                  }\n                } -->\n                <div id="btc-price-line-chart-container-en" class="chart-container" aria-label="Bitcoin 24-hour Price Line Chart"></div>\n                <div id="btc-price-text-analysis">\n                    <p>Bitcoin has sharply declined from its new all-time high of <strong><span class="highlight-value">$123,400 USD</span></strong> to <strong><span class="highlight-value">$117,400 USD</span></strong>.</p>\n                    <p>Significant selling pressure after the US PPI data pushed the price down. The current price is <strong><span class="highlight-value">$118,802 USD</span></strong>.</p>\n                    <p>Key support levels: <strong><span class="highlight-value">$118,000 – $117,500 USD</span></strong>. If 118k is lost, it could drop to 116k/112k.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id="institutional-whale-analysis-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-university" style="color: var(--icon-color-macro-legal);"></i> Institutional Flow & Whale Analysis</h2>\n        <div class="content-grid">\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Bitcoin ETF Data & Whale Activity</h3>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Inflows into spot Bitcoin ETFs are the main driver of Bitcoin's price momentum.</li>\n                    <li>Ethereum ETFs also attracted over <strong><span class="highlight-value">$1 billion USD</span></strong> in Q2 2025.</li>\n                    <li>Whale wallets holding 10,000-100,000 BTC control approximately <strong><span class="highlight-value">2/3 of the total supply</span></strong>, an increase of 4.1% over the past year.</li>\n                    <li>Flows from XRP whale wallets turned negative, with over <strong><span class="negative-text">$110 million USD in XRP</span></strong> transferred to Coinbase for liquidation.</li>\n                    <li>Only <strong><span class="highlight-value">14.5%</span></strong> of the total BTC supply is on exchanges (the lowest level since August 2018), indicating "smart money" accumulation.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </div>\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Corporate Treasuries & Institutional Trading Trends</h3>\n                <ul>\n                    <li><strong>MicroStrategy (Strategy):</strong> Holds over <strong><span class="highlight-value">628,900 BTC</span></strong> (worth nearly <strong><span class="highlight-value">$76 billion USD</span></strong>), accounting for approximately 3% of the total Bitcoin supply, continuing its accumulation strategy.</li>\n                    <li><strong>Bitmine Immersion Technologies Inc:</strong> Holds over <strong><span class="highlight-value">1.15 million ETH</span></strong> (approximately <strong><span class="highlight-value">$4.9 billion USD</span></strong>), making it the world's largest corporate Ether holder, with plans to acquire more.</li>\n                    <li>Institutional demand for Bitcoin is rapidly increasing; limited supply could cause a liquidity crisis.</li>\n                    <li>Major banks in Vietnam are also considering entering the digital asset market.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id="macro-analysis-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-globe-americas" style="color: var(--icon-color-macro-legal);"></i> In-depth Macro Analysis</h2>\n        <div class="content-grid">\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Fed Policy & Regulatory Framework</h3>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>US July PPI data increased by <strong><span class="highlight-value">0.9%</span></strong> (higher than forecast), complicating interest rate cut expectations.</li>\n                    <li>The probability of the Fed cutting interest rates by 0.25% in September decreased from <strong><span class="negative-text">99.8%</span></strong> to <strong><span class="negative-text">90.5%</span></strong>.</li>\n                    <li>The SEC has postponed its decision on approving Solana ETF proposals to October 2025.</li>\n                    <li>US President Donald Trump signed an executive order allowing 401(k) retirement accounts to hold cryptocurrencies, significantly expanding market access.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </div>\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3>Macroeconomic Indicators & Economic Calendar</h3>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Hot PPI data caused investors to lose over <strong><span class="negative-text">$170 billion USD</span></strong> in 24 hours.</li>\n                    <li>Gold is still considered a more reliable safe haven than Bitcoin during volatile stock market periods.</li>\n                    <li>US economic data (inflation, retail sales) and the expiration of over <strong><span class="highlight-value">$6.2 billion USD</span></strong> in Bitcoin, Ethereum, and XRP-related options contracts on August 15, 2025, create potential selling pressure.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n\n    <section id="top-coins-analysis-section">\n        <h2><i class="fas fa-coins" style="color: var(--icon-color-market-activity);"></i> Detailed Top Coins Analysis</h2>\n        <div class="content-grid">\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3><i class="fab fa-bitcoin" style="color: var(--icon-color-btc);"></i> Bitcoin (BTC)</h3>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Current Price: <strong><span class="highlight-value">$118,802 USD</span></strong> (<span class="negative-text">-4.03%</span> in 24h).</li>\n                    <li>Sharply declined from its historical peak of <strong><span class="highlight-value">$123,400 USD</span></strong> after US PPI data.</li>\n                    <li>Key support levels: <strong><span class="highlight-value">$118,000 – $117,500 USD</span></strong>. If 118k is lost, it could drop to 116k/112k.</li>\n                    <li>Long-term forecast: <strong><span class="highlight-value">75%</span></strong> chance of exceeding <strong><span class="highlight-value">$4.81 million USD</span></strong> by April 2036.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </div>\n            <div class="report-card">\n                <h3><i class="fab fa-ethereum" style="color: var(--icon-color-eth);"></i> Ethereum (ETH)</h3>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Current Price: <strong><span class="highlight-value">$4,568 USD</span></strong> (<span class="negative-text">-3.13%</span> in 24h).</li>\n                    <li>Affected after the Ethereum Foundation sold <strong><span class="negative-text">2,795 ETH ($127 million USD)</span></strong>.</li>\n                    <li>Sentiment remains bullish, with price forecasts potentially reaching <strong><span class="highlight-value">$5,000 USD</span></strong>, or even <strong><span class="highlight-value">$7,000 USD</span></strong> by the end of 2025.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class="report-card full-width">\n            <h3>Major Altcoin Performance (24h)</h3>\n            <div class="table-container">\n                <table class="crypto-table">\n                    <thead>\n                        <tr>\n                            <th>Coin</th>\n                            <th>Price</th>\n                            <th>24h Change</th>\n                        </tr>\n                    </thead>\n                    <tbody>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td data-label="Coin">Bitcoin (BTC)</td>\n                            <td data-label="Price">$118,802</td>\n                            <td data-label="24h Change" class="negative-text">-4.03%</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td data-label="Coin">Ethereum (ETH)</td>\n                            <td data-label="Price">$4,568</td>\n                            <